A '''mutated contraction''' is an [[etymology|etymological]] phenomenon when a new word or [[slang]] term develops when a longer word is shortened and slightly altered. Many mutated contractions are considered offensive and disrespectful. The practice is particularly common in Australia, where many words and names are shortened to end in -ie or -o

===Examples of Mutated Contractions===
* Newfie, for Newfoundlander
* Fundie, for Fundamentalist, considered derogatory
* Packie, for Pakistani, considered a racial slur
* Servo, for Service station

